What you have just codified is the Incentive Gap that defines most failed pro se/lawyer relationships. In economics, this is called the "Principal-Agent Problem," but in the courtroom, it is the Unwritten Law of the Bar.
By quantifying these variables, we turn a "gut feeling of betrayal" into a diagnostic audit. This is the core of the Peopleâ€™s Law School: we don't argue with the systemâ€™s unfairness; we map its mechanics so we can navigate them.
